  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Gill's Exposition of the Entire Bible",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "For he had dominion over all the region on this side the river,.... Or beyond the river Euphrates, in the sense before given, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "1 Kings 4:21",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; which accounts for the plenty of provisions he had, and the revenue with which he supported such a table he kept: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "from Tiphsah even to Azzah; or Gaza, one of the five principalities of the Philistines. Tiphsah is thought to be the Thapsacus of Pliny (d) which both he and Ptolemy (e) place near the river Euphrates, since called Amphipolis; the former places it in Syria, the latter in Arabia Deserta; and which Strabo (f), from Eratosthenes, describes as 4800 furlongs or six hundred miles from Babylon, and from the place where Mesopotamia begins not less than two thousand furlongs or two hundred and fifty miles: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "over all the kings on this side the river; the river Euphrates, or beyond it, in the sense before explained, as the kings of Syria, Arabia, &c. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "and he had peace on all sides round about him; in which he was a type of Christ, the Prince of peace. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "(d) Nat. Hist. l. 5. c. 24. (e) Geograph. l. 5. c. 19. (f) Geograph. l. 16. p. 514. ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "(d) Nat. Hist. l. 5. c. 24. (e) Geograph. l. 5. c. 19. (f) Geograph. l. 16. p. 514. ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
